note.S: Indo Chinese. Interesting menu. Finally had a chance to go and try out Fatt Pundit which is an Indian Chinese tapas sort of restaurant. The menu is quite different and there is definitely a good amount of vegetarian options. I've got to say was seriously impressed by the food.. the paneer wasnt your usual London type and mean that in a good way. The popcorn cauliflower and crispy okra salt n pepper were amazing too! The mix vegetable momos were super delicious but very similar to most dumplings you can get elsewhere. The only downside would have to be the mock chicken.. it was nice but I think @duckandricesoho have just set the bar way too high on that one. The cocktails were very different to your usual and amazing at the same time Normally don't opt for dessert but can you really say no to a siZzling brownie. mmmm can't wait to go back! Lastly, the vibe there was great but the service could have been a little faster.
